# Vodka Pasta

## Prepare the Sauce

> Use a large pot or a wok here, and everything comes together into this pot

- Olive Oil | 1/4 cup | 
- Italian Sausage |  | 

Cook sausage until brown, try to keep some bite-sized chunks instead of fully ground

- Garlic | 4 cloves | Minced
- Red Pepper Flakes | 1/2 tsp | 

Add garlic & red pepper once meat is brown. Cook until garlic is golden color

- Crushed Tomatoes (can) | 28 oz | 
- Salt | 3/4 tsp | 

Combine tomatoes and salt with meat, and bring to a boil

Lower heat to simmer for 15 minutes

## Meanwhile

- Linguini Noodles | 1 lb | 

Cook noodles al dente (about 8 minutes)

Drain and set aside

## After the Simmering

> In the tomato sauce pot

- Vodka | 2 tbsp (ie 1 shot) | 
- Heavy Whipping Cream | 1/2 cup | 

Add above ingredients, increase heat to medium until boiling

Combine noodles, stir for 1 minute

